          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target used was produced by evaporation of pure",
                " (99.99%) metallic 89-Y on a Ta backing.  Directly",
                "after this procedure, a thin layer of gold of 99.9999%",
                "purity was additionally evaporated on the target in",
                "order to prevent oxidization.  The thickness of the",
                "target used was 436+/-24 mug/cm2 for the 89-Y layer and",
                "125+/-7 mug/cm2 for the gold \"flush\".  The target was",
                "checked for possible deterioration after the end of the",
                "measurements and was found to be stable within 2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D4PI",
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma-single spectra were measured by",
                "means of a large 12 inches X 12 inches 4pi NaI(Tl)",
                "summing detector.  The NaI(Tl) detector consists of two",
                "scintillation crystals of cylindrical shape with a",
                "diameter of 305 mm and a length of 152.5 mm.  Each",
                "crystal is segmented in four equal parts wrapped with",
                "aluminum (0.5 mm thick).  With this detector",
                "arrangement, a solid angle of ~96% of 4pi covered for",
                "the gamma-rays emitted from the target at the",
                "crystals's center.  The main advantage of using such",
                "a 4pi detector is that, instead of measuring and",
                "analyzing numerous gamma-cascade transitions, one",
                "observes angle-integrated gamma-ray fluxes due to the",
                "4pi geometry covered by the summing crystal;  thus,",
                "systematic errors due to gamma-angular distribution",
                "effects are avoided."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to keep the dead time below 5%-7%,",
                "especially at Ep>3 MeV, it was necessary to work with",
                "beam currents of less than 300 nanoampere on target.",
                "The beam energy spread was <1.2 KeV at Ep=872 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainty of beam current integration."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainty of target thickness measurements."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total errors in the cross sections are of",
                "the order of 9%-12% except for those in the cross",
                "sections determined at the four lowest energies.  The",
                "latter errors range from 15% to 25%.  Apart from",
                "statistical errors of <3% at Ep>2.5 MeV and ~10%-15% at",
                " Ep<2.5 MeV.  Additional 6%-9% error in the simulated",
                "efficiency was also taken into account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  In order to avoid systematic errors in",
                "our analysis, only gamma-ray fluxes with photon",
                "energies above 8 MeV were used to determine the cross",
                "section of the reaction of interest."
              ]
            }
          ],
